text.tspan: Initial Contact: Taylor is starting to realize that she needs to
start planning for the future in terms of her estate. She is not
sure how to tackle this complicated task alone so she decides
to call somebody who is an expert on the matter, Dan Parrish.
She sets up an in person meeting, and is already starting to be
relieved.
Understanding: Taylor sits down with Dan as she introduces
her worries and her wishes for her estate. Dan asks key
questions to try and understand her wishes at a deep level. He
does this so that he can provide an innovative yet practical
solution that best fits his new client's needs.
Custom Solution: Now that Dan has all the information he needs
he starts diving into the project. He compares different services
to find the ones that best fit his client's wishes. This can involve
a variety of different insurance products and is always client
specific. His extensive knowledge and experience with estate
planning ensures his client's satisfaction.
Presentation: Dan has completed his insurance proposal to his
client and is ready to present it. He calls Taylor for a meeting
and details out his solution and how it directly solves all of her
wishes and worries. Dan makes sure that Taylor is happy and
if she has any more desires, he further tweaks his plan.
Finalize: Once Dan makes sure that Taylor is completely
satisfied with his plan, they finalize the agreement and the
real work can begin. At this time Taylor is feeling an
overwhelming sense of relief, knowing that her estate will
be protected, thanks to Dan's work.
